                <mxCell id="27" value="&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px&quot;&gt;First try to undertand how to approch this problem statement, as shown in figure and given example inputs we have 5 horizontal and 4 vertical lines.&lt;br&gt;Then there are two given array horizontalCuts and verticalCuts, shows plot lines horizontal and vertically respectivelly.&lt;br&gt;We have to find out maximum covered area that ploted from horizontal and vertical lines.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#fff;fontStyle=2;fontColor=#000;spacingTop=-32;verticalAlign=middle;" vertex="1" parent="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="440" y="437" width="240" height="283" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="29" value="&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px&quot;&gt;First we add hight and width in given array horizontalCuts and verticalCuts so if there are any array with single element then we have to a starting and ending point based on its previous value(Here added value of 5 as h and 4 as w and then sort so if any greater than existing value then h,v set as strting point else it will play role as ending value)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px&quot;&gt;Now we find maximum differnce of horizontalCuts and verticalCuts(here 2 and 2)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#fff;fontStyle=2;fontColor=#000;" vertex="1" parent="1">
